odal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Jan 04, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104hvg1704363446431.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/hvg1704363446431.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/hvg1704363446431.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"usv1665702837264\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Ensuring Referential Integrity\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"usv1665702837264__ensuring_referential_integrity_35618\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">You can ensure the referential integrity of data in Uniface applications by defining constraints in object properties, ProcScript, and database scripts.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"usv1665702837264__p_d10268e1_d10269e1_d10270e1\">Uniface provides the following mechanisms for ensuring referential integrity:</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"usv1665702837264__table_d1079e1_d1080e1_d1081e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Ensuring referential integrity</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"usv1665702837264__table_d1079e1_d1080e1_d1081e1__entry__1\">\n Constraints\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"usv1665702837264__table_d1079e1_d1080e1_d1081e1__entry__2\">\n How to implement\n </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"usv1665702837264__table_d1079e1_d1080e1_d1081e1__entry__1\">\n Declarative constraints\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"usv1665702837264__table_d1079e1_d1080e1_d1081e1__entry__2\">\n Create declarative definitions for relationships and foreign key rules in the modeled objects. If both entities in a relationship are correctly handled in the component data structure, Uniface automatically enforces the constraints you have defined for that relationship.\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"usv1665702837264__table_d1079e1_d1080e1_d1081e1__entry__1\">\n Database triggers via the Create Table facility\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"usv1665702837264__table_d1079e1_d1080e1_d1081e1__entry__2\">\n Use the Create Table facility to create database triggers that enforce delete constraints on the table in the database. This means that the constraints are enforced both when a Uniface application deletes a record and when a non-Uniface application deletes a record.\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"usv1665702837264__table_d1079e1_d1080e1_d1081e1__entry__1\">\n Customized constraints\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"usv1665702837264__table_d1079e1_d1080e1_d1081e1__entry__2\">\n Define these constraints using ProcScript in Uniface triggers (for example, the leaveModifiedKey trigger). This is a very specialized way of enforcing constraints in specific circumstances.\n </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"usv1665702837264__p_d10271e1_d10272e1_d10273e1\">For more information about whether your driver supports database referential integrity, consult the appropriate DBMS connector documentation.</p>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fnf1665702703926.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Referential Integrity</a><p>Referential integrity is a standard feature of relational database design that prevents users or applications from entering inconsistent data. Most relational databases have referential integrity rules that you can apply when you create a relationship between tables.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lsp1665702531534.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Database Connectors</a><p>To access, retrieve, and store data, Uniface provides database connectors that translate Uniface I/O requests into the target database's data definition and manipulation languages.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_5753865\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_5753865\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Ensuring Referential Integrity Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Jan 04, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Ensuring Referential Integrity You can ensure the referential integrity of data in Uniface applications by defining constraints in object properties, ProcScript, and database scripts. Uniface provides the following mechanisms for ensuring referential integrity: Table 1. Ensuring referential integrity Constraints How to implement Declarative constraints Create declarative definitions for relationships and foreign key rules in the modeled objects. If both entities in a relationship are correctly handled in the component data structure, Uniface automatically enforces the constraints you have defined for that relationship. Database triggers via the Create Table facility Use the Create Table facility to create database triggers that enforce delete constraints on the table in the database. This means that the constraints are enforced both when a Uniface application deletes a record and when a non-Uniface application deletes a record. Customized constraints Define these constraints using ProcScript in Uniface triggers (for example, the leaveModifiedKey trigger). This is a very specialized way of enforcing constraints in specific circumstances. For more information about whether your driver supports database referential integrity, consult the appropriate DBMS connector documentation. Related Links Referential Integrity Referential integrity is a standard feature of relational database design that prevents users or applications from entering inconsistent data. Most relational databases have referential integrity rules that you can apply when you create a relationship between tables. Database Connectors To access, retrieve, and store data, Uniface provides database connectors that translate Uniface I/O requests into the target database's data definition and manipulation languages. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}